<strong>BIBLIOGRAPHY ENTRY</strong>
<br><br>
Add a bibliography at the end of your essay citing all relevant sources used in your research, regardless of whether they are explicitly mentioned in your writing.
<br><br>
<strong>Format</strong>
<br>
<blockquote class="ref-hang-indent double-line-spacing">
	Author 1 (surname, given name), Author 2 (name in normal order), Author 3 (name in normal order), and Author 4 (name in normal order). <em>Title of Book</em>. Place of publication: Publisher, year of publication.
</blockquote>
<br>
<strong>Example</strong>
<br>
<blockquote class="ref-hang-indent double-line-spacing">
	<span class="hover" title="Author 1 (surname, given name), Author 2 (name in normal order), Author 3 (name in normal order), and Author 4 (name in normal order)">Larsen, Larry, Betty Brown, Carlos Chan, and Tamara Tahatai</span>. 
	<em><span class="hover" title="Title of Book">The Decline and Fall of the Modern Generation</span></em>. 
	<span class="hover" title="Place of publication">Sydney</span>: 
	<span class="hover" title="Publisher">New Media Press</span>, 
	<span class="hover" title="year of publication">2056</span>.
</blockquote>
