<strong>IN&#45;TEXT CITATION</strong>
<br><br>
Put a footnote number in your text to show when you are using another person&#8217;s ideas or words.
<br>
<blockquote class="in-text-citation">
	&hellip;has been recently identified.<sup>1</sup>
</blockquote>
<br>
This number directs your reader to a footnote at the bottom of your page.The footnote contains information about the work you are citing, including the author&#8217;s names, details of the work, and relevant page number(s).
<br><br>
<strong>FOOTNOTES</strong>
<br><br>
Footnotes are placed in numerical order at the bottom of the page.
<br>
When there are four or more authors, use the first author&#8217;s name followed by <strong>et al</strong>. (and others).
<br>
In the case of most assignment papers and essays where footnotes and a bibliography are used, the footnote citation details can be quite brief (Example B) because the full details are found in the bibliography. However if you are instructed by your tutor or lecturer to provide a full reference in the footnote the first time a work is cited, see Example A. If the work is cited again, use the short form (Example B).
<br>
When shortened references to the same work follow each other with no other references in&#45;between, replace the authors&#8217; name and title and publication details with <strong>ibid</strong> (Example C) and the page number if it differs from the previous citation (Example D).
<br><br>
<strong>Example A</strong>
<br>
<blockquote class="footnotes ref-indent-1-27cm">
	<span class="smaller">1. Larry Larsen et al., <em>The Decline and Fall of the Modern Generation</em> (Sydney: New Media Press, 2056), 78.</span>
</blockquote>
<br>
<strong>Example B</strong>
<br>
<blockquote class="footnotes ref-indent-1-27cm">
	<span class="smaller">7. Larsen et al., <em>Decline and Fall</em>, 43.</span>
</blockquote>
<br>
<strong>Example C</strong>
<br>
<blockquote class="footnotes ref-indent-1-27cm">
	<span class="smaller">8. Ibid.</span>
</blockquote>
<br>
<strong>Example D</strong>
<br>
<blockquote class="footnotes ref-indent-1-27cm">
	<span class="smaller">9. Ibid., 25&#45;6.</span>
</blockquote>
